<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When it comes to customer satisfaction, this exchange has a rather low rating of 1.8 on </span><a href="https://www.trustpilot.com/review/www.mexc.com" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trustpilot</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. For comparison, Binance sits even lower at 1.4. On a brighter note, MEXC boasts a perfect trust score of 10 out of 10 on CoinGecko, which takes into account factors like trading volume, liquidity depth, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">cybersecurity measures, and more.</span></p>
<h2><strong>How Do I Get Started with MEXC?</strong></h2>
<div class="b-cta-wrapper"><div class="b-cta b-cta--referral"><div class="b-cta__image"><a href="/recommends/mexc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" data-wpel-link="internal"><img decoding="async" width="300" height="300" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mexc-logo-300x300.jpg" class="image-fit image-fit--center wp-post-image" alt="mexc-logo" /></a></div><div class="b-cta__meta"><div class="promotion"><p class="title">Exclusive Benefits</p><p class="value">Up To $10,000 Sign Up Bonus</p><p>Up to 50% Off Trading Fees</p><p>Code Valid: June 2026</p></div><div class="referral-code"><input type="text" value="mexc-ventureburn" class="referral-code__input" readonly><button type="button" class="referral-code__btn btn btn-primary">Copy</button></div></div><div class="b-cta__btn d-flex flex-column align-items-center justify-content-center"><a href="/recommends/mexc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="btn btn-primary" data-wpel-link="internal"><span>Claim Bonus Now</span></a></div></div><!-- /.b-cta --></div>
<h3><strong>Step 1: Create Your MEXC Account With the Referral Code mexc-ventureburn</strong></h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mexc8.jpg" alt="Mexc register form" width="1355" height="803" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To get started, create your MEXC account. Simply visit the </span><a href="https://www.mexc.com/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC website</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and click on “Sign Up” located in the top right corner. The signup process is pretty straightforward and won’t take long at all. You can register using your email or your mobile number. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you&#8217;re filling out the registration form, keep an eye out for a section that says “Enter Referral Code,” then fill in the <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mexc-referral-code/" data-wpel-link="internal">MEXC referral code</a> in this field. Or if you click this <a href="https://www.mexc.com/acquisition/custom-sign-up?shareCode=mexc-ventureburn" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer">MEXC referral link</a>, the code might already appear automatically.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Just make sure to enter the referral code correctly—remember, it is case-sensitive. Don’t forget to create a strong password and keep it safe! After that, just agree to the terms and conditions and click on “Create an Account.”</span></p>
<h3><strong>Step 2: Complete MEXC KYC</strong></h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mexc9.jpg" alt="MEXC KYC" width="1568" height="596" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Just like many other cryptocurrency exchanges, MEXC requires you to go through a Know Your Customer (KYC) verification. This step is crucial for preventing fraud and ensuring that everyone can trade safely. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It typically involves uploading a government-issued ID or a selfie. Completing MEXC KYC gives you access to more features like increased withdrawals and bonuses. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Step 3: Deposit Funds</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC offers a range of deposit methods based on your region. For a complete list of what’s available, check out the “Buy Crypto” section on the MEXC website. You’ll typically find options like bank transfers, credit/debit card purchases (where possible), and peer-to-peer (P2P) trading.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The most common deposit method is with cryptocurrency. To deposit you’ll need to:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pick the cryptocurrency you want to deposit, like BTC, USDT, or ETH. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Next, select the blockchain network that corresponds with the wallet or exchange you’re using to send your funds (for example, ERC20, TRC20, or BEP20). It is important to choose the right network because sending to the wrong one could lead to a permanent loss of your funds.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC will create a unique deposit address for you, which includes a QR code and an alphanumeric string. Make sure to copy it accurately. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Then, head over to the withdrawal section of your external wallet or exchange, paste the deposit address, and confirm the transaction.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Typically, deposits appear within minutes, but keep in mind that the actual time can vary based on blockchain congestion. You can keep an eye on the progress in the “Transaction History” section.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Step 4: Start Trading</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you start trading on MEXC, it usually takes place in the spot market, where you can buy and sell digital assets such as Bitcoin, Ethereum, and many other tokens. As soon as you access the trading interface, you’ll find real-time price charts, an order book, and tools that help you place different kinds of orders. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For those interested in more advanced trading options, MEXC also provides futures trading, enabling you to trade contracts based on cryptocurrency prices. Above all, it’s essential to keep risk management as a key part of your strategy.</span></p>
<h2 data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">Is MEXC Safe? Security, Risk Control, and Regulations</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC has really dedicated itself to strengthening its security measures. On the tech side, they’ve implemented a wide range of industry-standard protections: cold wallets to keep most user funds offline (which helps minimize the risk of online hacks), SSL encryption to safeguard data during transit, and regular audits—like a recent penetration test by Hacken that revealed no critical or high-risk vulnerabilities in their mobile app. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">On the user side, MEXC provides several tools to help keep your account safe: two-factor authentication (2FA) through Google Authenticator or SMS, email verification, mobile verification, &#8220;anti-phishing&#8221; codes, and withdrawal whitelisting (which only permits withdrawals to wallet addresses you’ve approved). </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">They also keep an eye out for any suspicious activity, including fraud syndicate operations, bot trading, and various risk control measures.</span></p>
<h2><strong>Which Other Options are Available Besides MEXC </strong></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thinking about alternatives to MEXC? There are several crypto exchanges out there that bring strong features, solid security, and various trade-offs to the table. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many experts highlight OKX as one of the best overall options, thanks to its commitment to regulatory compliance, wide range of services, and reliable security measures. It offers everything from spot trading to futures, DeFi integration, and even its own Web3 wallet. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bybit is a go-to for those focused on derivatives and high-leverage trading, especially among seasoned traders. If you&#8217;re after features like futures, margin, or perpetual swaps, Bybit usually ranks high on the list. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance remains a giant in the crypto world, providing enormous liquidity, a vast selection of trading pairs, a global presence, and a variety of tools (like spot, margin, futures, staking, NFT marketplaces, etc.). If your priority is to find good liquidity and access to both popular and up-and-coming tokens, Binance is a strong contender. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KuCoin is a favorite among altcoin traders and those looking to dive into newer, smaller tokens, as well as token-launch initiatives.</span></p>
<h2><strong>MEXC Review: Final Thoughts</strong></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC has built a solid reputation as a versatile crypto exchange, particularly for traders who appreciate having access to a diverse range of tokens, low fees, and advanced features like futures and margin trading. The exchange is serious about user security, as seen by its ongoing improvements, including cold wallet storage, proof of reserves, fraud detection systems, and a growing insurance fund. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">However, it’s important to note that no platform is without its flaws. MEXC’s regulatory standing is inconsistent across different jurisdictions, with several financial authorities raising concerns about its unlicensed operations. This regulatory uncertainty, coupled with occasional user complaints regarding frozen accounts or delayed withdrawals, means that traders, especially in regions where MEXC faces restrictions, should be cautious. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ultimately, whether MEXC is the right choice for you depends on your individual priorities. If you value a wide selection of tokens and are comfortable taking charge of your own security practices, MEXC can be a powerful tool. </span></p>
<p>While MEXC offers competitive fees and a vast array of coins, regional suitability is key. For traders in South Asia comparing fee structures and compliance, it is worth seeing how MEXC ranks against other top contenders in our guide to the <a href="https://ventureburn.com/best-crypto-exchange-in-india/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b>best crypto exchange in India</b></a>.</p>
<h2 data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC Review FAQs and Further Questions</span></h2>
<h3><strong>Is MEXC a safe crypto exchange?</strong></h3>
<p>Many users and industry experts regard MEXC Exchange as a safe platform.It uses robust security features such as SSL encryption, cold storage, and multi-factor authentication (MFA). The exchange also offers a Futures Insurance Fund to safeguard user funds and data.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">An independent assessor has given the exchange a solid AA rating for security, with a score of over 86%.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Is MEXC a good crypto exchange?</strong></h3>
<p>Yes, MEXC is a good crypto exchange. But whether it’s right for you depends on your trading goals.</p>
<h3><strong>Does MEXC support fiat-to-crypto transactions?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">No. This exchange only allows you to trade crypto-to-crypto. Before trading, you can still purchase cryptocurrencies with fiat. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Is KYC verification mandatory on MEXC?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">KYC verification is a mandatory requirement for both new and existing users to access advanced features.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Is MEXC accessible to users in the United States?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">No. MEXC is not available for new users in the United States. Their terms clearly list the U.S. among the “Prohibited Countries/Regions.” So, even if you’ve seen the MEXC app listed in the U.S. App Store in the past, it doesn’t change the existing restrictions.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Where are MEXC headquarters?</strong></h3>
<p>MEXC’s headquarters are located in Victoria, Seychelles.</p>
<h3><strong>Can I transfer money from MEXC directly to my bank account?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you can transfer money (fiat) straight from MEXC to your bank account really depends on a few factors like your country, the level of verification on your account, and whether MEXC allows bank or fiat withdrawals in your area. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In many places, especially outside of Europe, MEXC doesn’t support direct fiat withdrawals to bank accounts. Most users have to convert their crypto to fiat on a platform that does allow bank withdrawals, or they might opt for peer-to-peer (P2P) methods instead.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Is MEXC a beginner-friendly platform?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes, MEXC is definitely beginner-friendly. Our MEXC review has demonstrated that the platform has a straightforward sign-up process, a user-friendly interface, and offers useful features like demo trading and educational resources, making it a great choice for newcomers.</span></p>
<h3><b data-path-to-node="4,6,3,0" data-index-in-node="1">Who owns mexc exchange</b>?</h3>
<p>Metin Mehmet Durgun founded the company, and John Chen Ju serves as the CEO.</p>
