										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>KGeN (Kratos Gamer Network) is a blockchain-based reputation system designed to connect gamers, developers, and their communities within the <b data-path-to-node="4,2,3,0" data-index-in-node="77">kgen crypto</b> ecosystem.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KGeN focuses on verified identity, fair reward systems, and unique distribution models, aiming to onboard millions users to Web3 gaming. This article covers all you need to know about this project including its foundation, tokenomics, airdrop system, and future roadmap.</span></p>
<h2><strong>What is KGeN?</strong></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KGeN</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, previously called<a href="https://kgen.io/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"> Kratos Gaming Network</a>, is a protocol for Web3 gaming that focuses on reputation and distribution, aiming to merge gaming, identity, and rewards into one cohesive experience.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The primary objective is to develop verifiable, data-rich profiles for gamers using Zero-Knowledge Machine Learning (zkML), allowing players to keep control over their data and identity.   </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Moreover, the project provides gamified tools for user acquisition and engagement, assisting game publishers in optimizing their acquisition costs and enhancing lifetime value. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This ultimately helped to grow the Web3 gaming landscape.</span></p>
<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>&gt;&gt;&gt; Read More: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/what-is-openledger/" data-wpel-link="internal">What Is OpenLedger? Project, Token, Airdrop, Roadmap Explained</a></strong></span></em></p>
<h2><strong>KGeN Five Key Dimensions </strong></h2>
<h3><strong>Proof of Human </strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Establishing that there’s a real person behind the user persona is key to building trust within the network. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Proof of Play </strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Measuring how much and how intensely a user engages with the game and KGeN platform gives us valuable insights into their habits and preferences. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_193363" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193363" class="wp-image-193363 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kgen2.jpg" alt="KGeN Five Key Dimensions " width="800" height="267" /><p id="caption-attachment-193363" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Kgen</p></div>
<h3><strong>Proof of Skill </strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Assessing a user’s abilities and expertise across various engagement types helps us recognize and celebrate their skill growth over time. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Proof of Commerce </strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Acknowledging the economic activities within the KGeN ecosystem allows us to capture users&#8217; contributions and transactions in the marketplace. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Proof of Social Network </strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Charting users&#8217; social interactions and connections within the community highlights their role and influence among their peers.</span></p>
<h3><strong>KGeN Team</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Manish Agarwal</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Co-Founder, Elder Council Member, and part of the founding leadership of KGeN. Previously, he was CEO of Nazara Technologies, which is a well-known gaming firm in India.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Ishank Gupta</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Co-Founder as well. He works alongside Manish in shaping strategy. He has experience in scaling consumer businesses across regions. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Sreenivas Makam</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Has 15+ years of experience in technology and data. Past roles include at Google and Cisco. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Dr. Mai Diab</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Holds a Ph.D. in Data Science (or Computer Engineering / related fields) and is a visiting lecturer. She brings academic and research leadership to the protocol.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Sukanya Vashist</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Has a legal and regulatory background. She has worked in e-commerce, logistics and fintech with companies like Lazada, Zomato, Udaan, etc. She helps with compliance, contracts, and regulatory strategy.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Mark Duscable</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Focused on innovation and digital product, and partnerships. His past roles include at Google and Coca-Cola. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Debashish Ghosh</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Is a brand and marketing expert. He previously worked as a VP in big media firms like Hotstar and Star India. He’ll be central to growth, branding, and community. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Sandeep Shetty</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Comes with gaming product leadership experience with Reliance Games. Therefore, he is a strong pick for building the gamer-facing product experience. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Shishir Sharma</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — 20+ years in internet and consumer business in emerging markets. His past roles are in major companies like Apple, HP, Whirlpool. He brings seasoned leadership especially navigating emerging markets. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Tariq Al Wari</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Deep analytics background in e-commerce and gaming. He also worked in transaction advisory. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Russell Araujo</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Financial services veteran. He has  experience with large renewal portfolios and so brings finance, risk and revenue management perspective. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Akshey Aggarwal</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> — Engineer with an MBA. He has experience building consumer-facing businesses in South Asia. </span></li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>KGeN Token</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For those following <b data-path-to-node="4,3,3,0" data-index-in-node="21">kgen token news</b>, the KGEN token serves as the primary utility token for the KGeN protocol, playing a key role in governance, protocol staking, incentive mechanics, and potentially oracles, among other uses. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">On the other hand, the </span><a href="https://kgen.gitbook.io/kgen/tokenomics/r-kgen" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">rKGEN</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> token is a reward token that’s been deployed on the Aptos blockchain before the Token Generation Event (TGE).</span></p>
<p data-start="107" data-end="267">It fully follows the Aptos Fungible Asset Standard (AFAS). Users earn rKGEN through their activity on the platform, making it a way to showcase contributions.</p>
<p data-start="269" data-end="497">You can stake rKGEN to earn rewards. Once the TGE occurs, you can exchange rKGEN for KGEN at a 1:1 ratio. The total KGEN supply caps at 1 billion tokens, with 40% allocated to the community. Of that, 8% will unlock at the TGE.</p>
<div id="attachment_193362" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193362" class="wp-image-193362 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kgen1.jpg" alt="KGeN Token" width="800" height="450" /><p id="caption-attachment-193362" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Kgen</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At the time of the TGE, 12.6% of the total token supply will be made available, not counting the amounts locked with exchanges or market makers. The team and investors will have their tokens locked up for four years.</span></p>
<h3><strong>KGeN Fundings</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KGeN has successfully raised a total of $43.5 million as of the latest funding round disclosed in September 2025. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The most recent round brought in $13.5 million and was strategically led by </span><a href="https://jumpcrypto.com/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jump Crypto</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, with support from Accel and Prosus Ventures. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Prior to this, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">KGeN</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://ventureburn.com/kgen-secures-13-5m-strategic-round-total-funding-climbs-to-43-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal"> secured $20 million in a seed round</a> back in January 2023. Then, in late 2024, they raised another $10 million during an ecosystem round, with key supporters including Aptos Foundation, Polygon Labs, Game7, and others. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Following the ecosystem round, KGeN&#8217;s fully diluted valuation was reported at $500 million. The seed round in 2023 was conducted at a fully diluted valuation of $150 million. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The funds are intended to enhance KGeN’s protocol infrastructure, known as the “Verified Distribution Protocol” or “VeriFi,” along with its identity and reputation framework (POGE), loyalty infrastructure, and commercial stack. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The company is also looking to expand into more markets, as the platform is already operational in over 60 countries. A portion of the funding will be used to speed up this global expansion.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>KGeN Roadmap</strong> </span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">While some details like exact timings, phase durations, intermediate metrics, and release dates remain undisclosed, the roadmap still provides a general overview. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The roadmap is partly aspirational, and some planned or in-progress features are not yet active. The GitBook (official documentation) contains a section titled &#8220;Future Roadmap&#8221; under the KGeN Foundation site. Examples of features on the future roadmap include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fully decentralizing the PoG and reputation infrastructure in several phases, ultimately involving node operators, decentralized storage, and performance-driven rewards.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Enhance the utility of the $KGEN token, strengthening its role in activities such as KGeN Play and the </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/kgen-secures-13-5m-strategic-round-total-funding-climbs-to-43-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400;">KGeN</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Gaming Oracle Network.</span></a></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Drive innovation by working alongside developers and partners to explore new token-based models, from tournaments and content creation to advanced reputation systems.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Empowering local communities by funding educational programs, supporting initiatives from clan leaders, and hosting community events. </span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KGeN has also made reference to a </span><a href="https://x.com/kgen_io/status/1960351116115501070" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">VeriFi Roadmap</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">(VeriFi = Verified Distribution Protocol) on social media to demonstrate its short and long-term objectives</span></p>
<h2><strong>How To Get KGeN Airdrop</strong></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Access </span><a href="https://play.kgen.io/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the website</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and log in with your Google account</span></p>
